<Head title="HTML Basics" description="CodingHome presents 'HTML Basics'!" author="AT Products LLC & CodingHome" />
<div id="page">
  <Navbar pageTitle="HTML Basics" 
    link={[
     { name: "CodingHome" , href: "/codinghome" },
    ]}
  />
  <div id="main-content">
    <Scrollspy id="html" 
      scrollcontent={[ 
        { name: "Example Document", href: "#example" },
        { name: "HTML Headings", href: "#head" },
        { name: "HTML Paragraphs", href: "#text" },
        { name: "HTML Links", href: "#links" },
        { name: "HTML Images", href: "#img" },
      ]} 
    >
      <Fragment slot="scrollspy-content">
        <div id="intro" class="story-top-scroll">
          <h1 class="text-start">HTML Basics</h1>
          <h5><b>Made by:</b> <a href="/codinghome">CodingHome</a>.</h5>
          <h5><b>Published by:</b> <a href="/">AT Products LLC</a>.</h5>
          <a href="../resources/#webresources" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" class="mt-2 btn btn-info">Web Resources</a>
          <hr>
        </div>
        <div id="content">
          <div id="example">
            <h3>Example Document</h3>
<pre><code>
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;My first Heading&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;My first paragraph&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code></pre>
            <p>The <code>&lt;!DOCTYPE&gt;</code> declaration represents the document type, and helps browsers to display web pages correctly. It must only appear once, at the top of the page (before any HTML tags). The <code>&lt;!DOCTYPE&gt;</code> declaration is not case sensitive. </p>
          </div>
          <div id="head">
            <h3>HTML Headings</h3>
            <p>HTML headings are defined with the <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> tags.
            <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code>defines the most important heading. <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> defines the least important heading:<br>
<pre><code>
&lt;h1&gt;Big&lt;/h1&gt;<br>
&lt;h6&gt;Small&lt;/h6&gt;
</code></pre> </p>
          </div>
          <div id="text">
            <h3>HTML Paragraphs</h3>
            <p>HTML paragraphs are defined with the <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tag:
<pre><code>
&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;<br>
&lt;p&gt;This is another paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
</code></pre>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div id="links">
            <h3>HTML Links</h3>
            <p>HTML links are defined with the &lt;a&gt; tag:<br>
            <pre><code>&lt;a href="https://example.com"&gt;This is a link&lt;/a&gt;</code></pre></p>
          </div>
          <div id="img">
            <h3>HTML Images</h3>
            <p>HTML images are defined with the &lt;img&gt; tag. The source file (src), alternative text (alt), width, and height are provided as attributes:<br>
            <pre><code>&lt;img src="example.jpg" alt="example.com" width="104" height="142"&gt;</code></pre></p>
          </div>  
        </div>
